<item>
            <title>[LU-4225] Test failure on test suite sanity, subtest test_120g</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4225</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Bob Glossman &amp;lt;bob.glossman@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/c3bd9340-4760-11e3-bbc4-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/c3bd9340-4760-11e3-bbc4-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This seems to be a very occasional random failure.  Searching maloo finds a total of 3 instances, each about 4 months apart.  No known cause.  From the client log it looks like the subtest completed and should have returned 0, not 1.  Maybe I&apos;m reading the log wrong.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_120g failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;test_120g returned 1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: sanity 120g&lt;/p&gt;</description>
